{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:john.7",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "John 7",
    "summary": "Source text for John 7 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:1",
      "text": "After these things, Jesus was walking in Galilee, for he wouldn’ t walk in Judea, because the Jews sought to kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:2",
      "text": "Now the feast of the Jews, the Feast of Booths, was at hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:3",
      "text": "His brothers therefore said to him, “ Depart from here and go into Judea, that your disciples also may see your works which you do.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:4",
      "text": "For no one does anything in secret while he seeks to be known openly. If you do these things, reveal yourself to the world.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:5",
      "text": "For even his brothers didn’ t believe in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:6",
      "text": "Jesus therefore said to them, “ My time has not yet come, but your time is always ready.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:7",
      "text": "The world can ’ t hate you, but it hates me, because I testify about it, that its works are evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:8",
      "text": "You go up to the feast. I am not yet going up to this feast, because my time is not yet fulfilled.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:9",
      "text": "Having said these things to them, he stayed in Galilee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:10",
      "text": "But when his brothers had gone up to the feast, then he also went up, not publicly, but as it were in secret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:11",
      "text": "The Jews therefore sought him at the feast, and said, “ Where is he?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:12",
      "text": "There was much murmuring among the multitudes concerning him. Some said, “ He is a good man.” Others said, “ Not so, but he leads the multitude astray.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:13",
      "text": "Yet no one spoke openly of him for fear of the Jews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:14",
      "text": "But when it was now the middle of the feast, Jesus went up into the temple and taught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:15",
      "text": "The Jews therefore marveled, saying, “ How does this man know letters, having never been educated?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:16",
      "text": "Jesus therefore answered them, “ My teaching is not mine, but his who sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:17",
      "text": "If anyone desires to do his will, he will know about the teaching, whether it is from God or if I am speaking from myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:18",
      "text": "He who speaks from himself seeks his own glory, but he who seeks the glory of him who sent him is true, and no unrighteousness is in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:19",
      "text": "Didn’ t Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keeps the law? Why do you seek to kill me?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:20",
      "text": "The multitude answered, “ You have a demon! Who seeks to kill you?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:21",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “ I did one work and you all marvel because of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:22",
      "text": "Moses has given you circumcision (not that it is of Moses, but of the fathers), and on the Sabbath you circumcise a boy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:23",
      "text": "If a boy receives circumcision on the Sabbath, that the law of Moses may not be broken, are you angry with me because I made a man completely healthy on the Sabbath?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:24",
      "text": "Don’ t judge according to appearance, but judge righteous judgment.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:25",
      "text": "Therefore some of them of Jerusalem said, “Isn’ t this he whom they seek to kill?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:26",
      "text": "Behold, he speaks openly, and they say nothing to him. Can it be that the rulers indeed know that this is truly the Christ?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:27",
      "text": "However, we know where this man comes from, but when the Christ comes, no one will know where he comes from.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:28",
      "text": "Jesus therefore cried out in the temple, teaching and saying, “ You both know me, and know where I am from. I have not come of myself, but he who sent me is true, whom you don’ t know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:29",
      "text": "I know him, because I am from him, and he sent me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:30",
      "text": "They sought therefore to take him; but no one laid a hand on him, because his hour had not yet come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:31",
      "text": "But of the multitude, many believed in him. They said, “ When the Christ comes, he won’ t do more signs than those which this man has done, will he?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:32",
      "text": "The Pharisees heard the multitude murmuring these things concerning him, and the chief priests and the Pharisees sent officers to arrest him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:33",
      "text": "Then Jesus said, “ I will be with you a little while longer, then I go to him who sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:34",
      "text": "You will seek me and won’t find me. You can ’t come where I am.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:35",
      "text": "The Jews therefore said among themselves, “ Where will this man go that we won’ t find him? Will he go to the Dispersion among the Greeks and teach the Greeks?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:36",
      "text": "What is this word that he said, ‘ You will seek me, and won’ t find me;’ and ‘ Where I am, you can ’ t come ’?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:37",
      "text": "Now on the last and greatest day of the feast, Jesus stood and cried out, “ If anyone is thirsty, let him come to me and drink!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:38",
      "text": "He who believes in me, as the Scripture has said, from within him will flow rivers of living water.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:39",
      "text": "But he said this about the Spirit, which those believing in him were to receive. For the Holy Spirit was not yet given, because Jesus wasn’ t yet glorified.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:40",
      "text": "Many of the multitude therefore, when they heard these words, said, “ This is truly the prophet.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:41",
      "text": "Others said, “ This is the Christ.” But some said, “ What, does the Christ come out of Galilee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:42",
      "text": "Hasn’ t the Scripture said that the Christ comes of the offspring of David, and from Bethlehem, the village where David was?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:43",
      "text": "So a division arose in the multitude because of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:44",
      "text": "Some of them would have arrested him, but no one laid hands on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:45",
      "text": "The officers therefore came to the chief priests and Pharisees; and they said to them, “ Why didn’ t you bring him?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:46",
      "text": "The officers answered, “ No man ever spoke like this man!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.47",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:47",
      "text": "The Pharisees therefore answered them, “ You aren’ t also led astray, are you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.48",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:48",
      "text": "Have any of the rulers or any of the Pharisees believed in him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.49",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:49",
      "text": "But this multitude that doesn’ t know the law is cursed.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.50",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:50",
      "text": "Nicodemus (he who came to him by night, being one of them) said to them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.51",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:51",
      "text": "“ Does our law judge a man unless it first hears from him personally and knows what he does?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.52",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:52",
      "text": "They answered him, “ Are you also from Galilee? Search and see that no prophet has arisen out of Galilee.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.7.53",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:53",
      "text": "Everyone went to his own house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
